@PotatoJesus  the whole React model makes it difficult for child components to talk to their parents.  One solution is to send via props, a function in the parent.  For example:

//in parent component:

parentFunction(){
  //do stuff and have access to parent stuff
}

render(){
   return <Child refToFunction={this.parentFunction}/>
}


//in child, to trigger the parent function:
this.props.refToFunction();

